r />IOW, if your issue is that you re-mount things read-only for backups<br />and then remount it rw again soon afterwards, but it's not actually<br />_unmounted_, maybe you could instead just add a flag to the 'struct<br />super_block' saying "this mount has been warned about already"?<br /><br />That would seem to make sense regardless. No? Partoicularly since we<br />also don't want to warn multiple times just because the same thing<br />gets mounted in multiple places.<br /><br />Of course, if you actually unmount and completely re-mount a<br />filesystem, then that would still warn multiple times, but at that<br />point I think it's reasonable to do.<br /><br />                Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
